title: PGA Tour agrees to merge with Saudi-backed rival LIV Golf
description: The PGA Tour has agreed to merge with its Saudi-backed rival LIV Golf.

title: Chinese 'police stations' in UK are 'unacceptable'
description: The Chinese embassy has been told running overseas police stations in the UK is "unacceptable" and that "they must not operate in any form".

title: Pope Francis in hospital for check-up
description: Pope Francis has gone to Rome's Gemelli hospital for a check-up.

title: Hong Kong government seeks court injunction to ban protest song
description: Hong Kong's government has asked a court to ban a popular song which became an unofficial anthem for the 2019 pro-democracy protests.

title: Mother pardoned for child deaths says release is 'win for science'
description: The Australian mother jailed for 20 years over the deaths of her four children says her release is a major victory for "science and especially truth".

title: Jim Hines - first sprinter to run 100m in under 10 seconds - dies aged 76
description: Jim Hines, the first man to break the 10-second barrier for the 100 metres, has died aged 76.

title: About ducking time: Apple to tweak iPhone autocorrect function
description: Apple has announced it will upgrade its autocorrect feature so it no longer changes one of the most common expletives to the word "ducking".

title: Ukraine war: Flooding fears after major dam hit by shelling in Russia-controlled Kherson region
description: A dam in the Russian controlled part of southern Ukraine has been damaged by shelling, leading to flooding in the area already hit by months of conflict.
